    "lyrics": {
      "text": "Save us, O Son__ of God, Who art won-drous__ in the Saints, who chant to Thee:__ Al-le-lu--i-a. \n\nSave us, O Son__ of God, Who art won-drous__ in the Saints, who chant to Thee:__ Al-le-lu--i-a. \n\nSave us, O Son__ of God, Who art won-drous__ in the Saints, who chant to Thee:__ Al-le-lu--i-a. \n\nSave us, O Son__ of God, Who art won-drous__ in the Saints, who chant to Thee:__ Al-le-lu--i-a. \n\nBoth now and ev-er, and un-to the ag-es of ag-es. A-men.\n\nOn-ly-be-got-ten Son and Word of God, Thou Who art im-mor----tal, and didst deign for our sal-va--tion to be-come in-car-nate of the ho-ly The-o-to--kos and Ev-er-vir-gin Mar--y, with-out change be-com-ing man, and Who wast cru-ci-fied, O Christ__ God, by__ death tram--pling down death: Thou Who art one of the Ho--ly Trin--i-ty, glo-ri-fied to-geth-er with the Fa-ther and the Ho-ly Spir----it, save____ us.___"
